<br>
I currently solo Frost Giant Berserker with little trouble and they are 37-41.  These guys should be easy especially if we group up against them.  <br>
<br>
The night you guys were in KD with the giants Eimi and I started working on a new tactic.  We were very successfully using a game of reverse fear kiting with Frost Giant Scouts.  She would pull, I snared and then I unloaded with the big guns.  Eimi chased the giant who was chasing me because I was unloading with an occasional bomb.  Even though Eimi didn’t feel she was helping much, I was using little more than half the mana I normally take to kill these guys.  <br>
<br>
We had a few close calls.  One very close and twice she got lower than we wanted because of possible adds.  Her FD was very useful in allowing me to pick up the MoB and finish.  The scouts are 33–36 and these guys are much tougher so I am sure Eimi would not be able to tank them.  However, Hikanur will fit that position well.  <br>
<br>
Menludarja, you hunted in Everfrost a lot.  Does this sound possible?  Can we do this or should we try to pick up a larger group and jump them with normal methods?  <br>
<br>
Just wondering if anyone was interested.  One note, this is open to all but anyone under 33rd may not get experience.  <br>
